  "prompt_text": "What should I eat to improve my digestion?",
  "provider": "anthropic",
  "model": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
  "response_text": "# Foods that support digestion\n\n**Fiber-rich options:**\n- Whole grains, oats, and legumes\n- Vegetables (especially leafy greens and broccoli)\n- Fruits with skins (apples, pears, berries)\n\n**Fermented foods:**\n- Yogurt, kefir, or other probiotics\n- Sauerkraut, kimchi, miso\n- Kombucha\n\n**Easy-to-digest proteins:**\n- Eggs, fish, chicken\n- Tofu, tempeh\n\n**Other helpful foods:**\n- Ginger and turmeric (anti-inflammatory)\n- Bone broth or vegetable broths\n- Healthy fats (olive oil, avocado, nuts)\n\n**General tips:**\n- Eat slowly and chew thoroughly\n- Stay hydrated\n- Limit processed foods, excess fat, and caffeine\n- Eat at regular times\n\n**When to seek help:**\nIf you have persistent digestive issues, it's worth talking to a doctor or registered dietitian—they can identify specific causes and give personalized advice.\n\nWhat digestive symptoms are you experiencing? That might help narrow down what would work best for you.",
